Chrysler Corp's Chrysler Motors unitsaid it will put four of its U.S. assembly plants on overtimeduring the week of March 16.    Three of the plants will also operate Saturday, March 14,beyond the normal five-day work week.    Chrysler facilities at Newark, Del., Sterling Heights,Mich., Warren, Mich., and the Jefferson plant in Detroit willwork overtime hours during the week. Newark, Sterling Heightsand Jefferson will work Saturday. Reuter&#3;